<subSubSection lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="449" pageId="8" pageNumber="447" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,151,896]" pageId="8" pageNumber="447">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,441,151,176]" pageId="8" pageNumber="447">Description of male.</emphasis>
Body length 
<quantity box="[593,683,152,176]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.4" pageId="8" pageNumber="447" unit="mm" value="8.4">8.4 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[694,758,151,176]" pageId="8" pageNumber="447">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[774,858,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 31–35" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1964,1987]" captionTargetBox="[177,1408,936,1951]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[177,1409,936,1953]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 31–35. Amazunculus bethoi sp. nov. Holotype male. 31, Habitus, left lateral view; 32, Antenna; 33, Wing; 34, Abdomen, dorsal view; 35, Holotype labels." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2632251/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="447">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
). Eyes contiguous for a distance of eighteen facets. F, EM, V = 
<quantity box="[296,387,188,213]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="447" unit="mm" value="0.6">0.6 mm</quantity>
, 
<quantity box="[401,492,188,213]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="447" unit="mm" value="0.6">0.6 mm</quantity>
, 
<quantity box="[507,599,188,212]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="447" unit="mm" value="0.4">0.4 mm</quantity>
. Frontal triangle brown pruinose. Face grey pruinose. Postcranium dark, brown pruinose dorsally and grey pruinose laterally and ventrally. Antennae (
<figureCitation box="[1058,1143,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 31–35" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1964,1987]" captionTargetBox="[177,1408,936,1951]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[177,1409,936,1953]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 31–35. Amazunculus bethoi sp. nov. Holotype male. 31, Habitus, left lateral view; 32, Antenna; 33, Wing; 34, Abdomen, dorsal view; 35, Holotype labels." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2632251/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="447">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
) with scape dark brown; pedicel dark brown, with four dorsal and six ventral bristles; postpedicel light brown with apex rounded below. LPP/WPP = 1.6. Labellum brown. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[545,641,295,320]" pageId="8" pageNumber="447">Thorax.</emphasis>
Postpronotal lobe dark brown, brown pruinose. Scutum and scutellum dark brown to black with brown pruinescence. Notopleuron concolorous with the scutum, brown pruinose. Mesopleuron black, brown pruinose, except the anepisternum with grey pruinescence anterodorsally in certain lights; katatergite with sparse grey pruinescence, anatergite brown pruinose; mediotergite black with brown pruinescence. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[316,381,439,464]" pageId="8" pageNumber="447">Wing</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[400,488,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURES 31–35" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1964,1987]" captionTargetBox="[177,1408,936,1951]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[177,1409,936,1953]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 31–35. Amazunculus bethoi sp. nov. Holotype male. 31, Habitus, left lateral view; 32, Antenna; 33, Wing; 34, Abdomen, dorsal view; 35, Holotype labels." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2632251/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="447">Fig. 33</figureCitation>
). Length 
<quantity box="[604,697,440,463]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.7" pageId="8" pageNumber="447" unit="mm" value="7.7">7.7 mm</quantity>
. LW/MWW = 3.3. LTC/LFC = 1.5. Membrane mostly hyaline except by basal third brown darkened. Halter with stem light brown and knob dark brown. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1172,1228,476,501]" pageId="8" pageNumber="447">Legs</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1244,1327,476,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 31–35" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1964,1987]" captionTargetBox="[177,1408,936,1951]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[177,1409,936,1953]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 31–35. Amazunculus bethoi sp. nov. Holotype male. 31, Habitus, left lateral view; 32, Antenna; 33, Wing; 34, Abdomen, dorsal view; 35, Holotype labels." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2632251/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="447">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
). All legs dark brown to black, except apices of trochanters, apices of the femora and bases of the tibiae yellowish brown; mid femora with dense setae on posterior face; femora with brown pruinescense on posterior face. Pulvilli yellow. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,268,583,608]" pageId="8" pageNumber="447">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[287,375,583,608]" captionStart="FIGURES 31–35" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1964,1987]" captionTargetBox="[177,1408,936,1951]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[177,1409,936,1953]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 31–35. Amazunculus bethoi sp. nov. Holotype male. 31, Habitus, left lateral view; 32, Antenna; 33, Wing; 34, Abdomen, dorsal view; 35, Holotype labels." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2632251/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="447">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
). Slightly wider than long. Black, all tergites with dark brown pruinescence anteriorly and interrupted bands of light brown pruinescence posteriorly. Tergites 6, 7 and sternites 6 and 7 as in 
<figureCitation box="[1344,1432,620,645]" captionStart="FIGURES 36–45" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1914,1937]" captionTargetBox="[220,1366,200,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[219,1374,193,1901]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 36–45. Amazunculus bethoi sp. nov. Holotype male. 36, Tergites 6, 7 and sternites 6, 7, ventral view; 37, Syntergosternite 8, posterior view; 38, Terminalia, dorsal view; 39, Surstyli, dorsal view; 40, Left surstylus, lateral view; 41, Right surstylus, lateral view; 42, Hypandrium, phallic guide and phallus, ventral view; 43, Phallic guide, dorsal view; 44, Hypandrium, phallic guide, phallus and ejaculatory apodeme, left lateral view; 45, Phallus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2632253/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="447">Fig. 36</figureCitation>
. Syntergosternite 8 mostly brown pruinose; about 0.4× length of tergite 5 (
<figureCitation box="[1014,1099,655,680]" captionStart="FIGURES 31–35" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1964,1987]" captionTargetBox="[177,1408,936,1951]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[177,1409,936,1953]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 31–35. Amazunculus bethoi sp. nov. Holotype male. 31, Habitus, left lateral view; 32, Antenna; 33, Wing; 34, Abdomen, dorsal view; 35, Holotype labels." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2632251/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="447">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
) and with a relatively small, circular membranous area (
<figureCitation box="[462,547,692,717]" captionStart="FIGURES 36–45" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1914,1937]" captionTargetBox="[220,1366,200,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[219,1374,193,1901]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 36–45. Amazunculus bethoi sp. nov. Holotype male. 36, Tergites 6, 7 and sternites 6, 7, ventral view; 37, Syntergosternite 8, posterior view; 38, Terminalia, dorsal view; 39, Surstyli, dorsal view; 40, Left surstylus, lateral view; 41, Right surstylus, lateral view; 42, Hypandrium, phallic guide and phallus, ventral view; 43, Phallic guide, dorsal view; 44, Hypandrium, phallic guide, phallus and ejaculatory apodeme, left lateral view; 45, Phallus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2632253/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="447">Fig. 37</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[569,707,692,717]" pageId="8" pageNumber="447">Terminalia.</emphasis>
Epandrium and surstyli yellowish brown (
<figureCitation box="[1195,1328,692,717]" captionStart="FIGURES 36–45" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1914,1937]" captionTargetBox="[220,1366,200,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[219,1374,193,1901]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 36–45. Amazunculus bethoi sp. nov. Holotype male. 36, Tergites 6, 7 and sternites 6, 7, ventral view; 37, Syntergosternite 8, posterior view; 38, Terminalia, dorsal view; 39, Surstyli, dorsal view; 40, Left surstylus, lateral view; 41, Right surstylus, lateral view; 42, Hypandrium, phallic guide and phallus, ventral view; 43, Phallic guide, dorsal view; 44, Hypandrium, phallic guide, phallus and ejaculatory apodeme, left lateral view; 45, Phallus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2632253/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="447">Figs 38–39</figureCitation>
). Surstyli (
<figureCitation box="[159,293,727,752]" captionStart="FIGURES 36–45" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1914,1937]" captionTargetBox="[220,1366,200,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[219,1374,193,1901]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 36–45. Amazunculus bethoi sp. nov. Holotype male. 36, Tergites 6, 7 and sternites 6, 7, ventral view; 37, Syntergosternite 8, posterior view; 38, Terminalia, dorsal view; 39, Surstyli, dorsal view; 40, Left surstylus, lateral view; 41, Right surstylus, lateral view; 42, Hypandrium, phallic guide and phallus, ventral view; 43, Phallic guide, dorsal view; 44, Hypandrium, phallic guide, phallus and ejaculatory apodeme, left lateral view; 45, Phallus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2632253/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="447">Figs 38–39</figureCitation>
) symmetrical, slightly pointed at apex, fused with epandrium, distinctly projected ventrally and surpassing the lateral margins of epandrium in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[841,974,764,789]" captionStart="FIGURES 36–45" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1914,1937]" captionTargetBox="[220,1366,200,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[219,1374,193,1901]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 36–45. Amazunculus bethoi sp. nov. Holotype male. 36, Tergites 6, 7 and sternites 6, 7, ventral view; 37, Syntergosternite 8, posterior view; 38, Terminalia, dorsal view; 39, Surstyli, dorsal view; 40, Left surstylus, lateral view; 41, Right surstylus, lateral view; 42, Hypandrium, phallic guide and phallus, ventral view; 43, Phallic guide, dorsal view; 44, Hypandrium, phallic guide, phallus and ejaculatory apodeme, left lateral view; 45, Phallus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2632253/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="447">Figs 40–41</figureCitation>
). Phallic guide (
<figureCitation box="[1161,1291,764,789]" captionStart="FIGURES 36–45" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1914,1937]" captionTargetBox="[220,1366,200,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[219,1374,193,1901]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 36–45. Amazunculus bethoi sp. nov. Holotype male. 36, Tergites 6, 7 and sternites 6, 7, ventral view; 37, Syntergosternite 8, posterior view; 38, Terminalia, dorsal view; 39, Surstyli, dorsal view; 40, Left surstylus, lateral view; 41, Right surstylus, lateral view; 42, Hypandrium, phallic guide and phallus, ventral view; 43, Phallic guide, dorsal view; 44, Hypandrium, phallic guide, phallus and ejaculatory apodeme, left lateral view; 45, Phallus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2632253/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="447">Figs 42–44</figureCitation>
) long, about 1.6× the hypandrium length; trifid at apex and with a pronounced medial curvature in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[1276,1359,799,824]" captionStart="FIGURES 36–45" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1914,1937]" captionTargetBox="[220,1366,200,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[219,1374,193,1901]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 36–45. Amazunculus bethoi sp. nov. Holotype male. 36, Tergites 6, 7 and sternites 6, 7, ventral view; 37, Syntergosternite 8, posterior view; 38, Terminalia, dorsal view; 39, Surstyli, dorsal view; 40, Left surstylus, lateral view; 41, Right surstylus, lateral view; 42, Hypandrium, phallic guide and phallus, ventral view; 43, Phallic guide, dorsal view; 44, Hypandrium, phallic guide, phallus and ejaculatory apodeme, left lateral view; 45, Phallus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2632253/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="447">Fig. 44</figureCitation>
).Basal processes of phallus large, surpassing posterior margin of hypandrium, slightly wider than hypandrium (
